<h1>What's Happened Lately</h1>
<h2>April 2026 - Broke My Fibula</h2>
<p>Broke it while skateboarding. This sucks.<br>While trying to go up and down an incline, I landed on my ankle and ended up fracturing my fibula into three pieces.</p> 
<img src="img/ironic.jpg" width="300">

<p>As of the time that I'm typing this, I'm in my UNIX Programming class in a wheelchair, later I'm about to swap it out for a knee scooter. Using the wheelchair puts a lot of strain on my arms.<p>

<p>Take this entry as a testimony or something to my stubborn hope. Even if everything kinda sucks now, for some reason I still believe it'll work out somehow, even if it's not the way I want it to and if I can barely walk.<br>And for the love of God, if you're skating up and down an incline, take a leaf out of my book and make sure you get the hang of your balancing first.</p> 

<p>I'm still going strong.<br>I've wondered when the first time I might break a bone would be. At least I did it while doing something cool.</p>

